headline: Janux Therapeutics Reports Second Quarter 2025 Financial Results and Business Highlights
summary: SAN DIEGO, August 07, 2025--Janux Therapeutics, Inc. (Nasdaq: JANX) (Janux), a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company developing a broad pipeline of novel immunotherapies by applying its proprietary technologies to its Tumor Activated T Cell Engager (TRACTr), Tumor Activated Immunomodulator (TRACIr), and Adaptive Immune Response Modulator (ARM) platforms, today reported financial results for the second quarter ended June 30, 2025, and provided a business update.

headline: Health Care Roundup: Market Talk
summary: 0804 GMT – Germany’s Merck KGaA reported second-quarter results that fell short of expectations at the top and bottom lines due to a weaker performance from the group’s electronics segment, Morgan Stanley analysts say in a research note.  The German life-sciences and chemicals group reported net sales that were 1% below consensus estimates, and Ebitda before exceptional items that missed forecasts by 4%, the analysts say.  Stronger expectations for Merck’s life-science and healthcare segments lead the group to raise its full-year guidance for organic growth in adjusted Ebitda, Morgan Stanley says.
